Firiona Vie is not an easy server to play.  It takes an understanding of the game, and the ability to push your class to its limits in order to survive and progress.<br>
<br>
The TLC helps to keep the population of the server down.  Most people don't wanna play somewhere when they can not get what they want when they want it.  It causes you to have to think and plan if you want an item.  It discourages farming.  Not having items no drop is wonderful.  That way, if someone misses an item that they need, maybe someone else has it.  Please note:  when I killed one of my epic mobs the other day, the item was Lore and No Drop. <br>
<br>
 I have had a GREAT experience with a customer service rep on this server- something that never happened during the two years I was on Prexus. <br>
<br>
The language situation I believe adds to the roleplaying situation of the server; why would a halfling and an Ogre know to speak to one another except for the halfling to say &quot;eeek&quot; and the Ogre to say &quot;yum.&quot;  The language situation is kinda difficult.  Sometimes people approach me and I can not understand them or offer to help.  All I can do is sow them and leave.<br>
<br>
There is room on this server for the roleplayers and those who want to be &quot;the first.&quot;  There are several guilds which are large enough to do big things, and plently of independent people running around just making nuisances of themselves.  You have a choice on which direction that you can go here.  I like the fact that for a husband-wife team (my situation), this server rocks for the two of us to spend a fun afternoon exploring and trying new quests or new adventures.  However, <br>
because the server population is small, it is hard for a single random person to find a group- last night, I saw 13 people in Dawnshroud peaks; with the exception of a newbie zone, that is the most people I have ever seen in one zone.  <br>
<br>
I love the automatic anon tag, and yet I hate it.  Lost a corpse the other day, and would have loved to send a bard a tell &quot;wanna earn some pp and find a corpse?&quot; only I did not know who the bards were, nor could I shout in the zone for one (there was two other people besides me anyway).  However, as a druid, it is great to not get constant teleport requests; I can do drive-by sows if I feel like it or offer to teleport if I so chose.  I have seen how it is on a larger server, and it can be heartbreaking to watch a druid friend get pestered and insulted for not teleporting.<br>
<br>
Because I don't know what is being used for which quest or I have an item that I suspect someone needs, my bank account is constantly full of moss, smelly hides, and miscellaneous minerals.  I think that the banker hates me.  <br>
<br>
So I think that while the TLC, low server population, lanugage, and the ANON tags have their problem, I also think that there is a plus side.  I would be hard pressed to call anything &quot;good&quot; or &quot;bad&quot; on this server because each has its own strengths and weaknesses.   I just think that being here, one has recognize that everything has its strengths and weaknesses, and if we change any part of what is present, then we are not really that much different from any other blue server.<br>
<br>
Scully Skywatcher<br>
