<br>
I now have a number of friends I group with on a daily basis and we are all of like temperament and game playing style. I absolutely love this server, but because it is so different from the regular blue servers, I think it requires a bit of a different play style. It made me actually strive to cultivate friendships here and I'm the better for it.  If I hadn't taken the time out from leveling, to actually get to know the people around me,  I think I would've gotten very bored and frustrated very fast. If you see someone in need, help them and remember those that helped you when you were in need.<br>
<br>
If you group with someone and find you group well with them, keep their name in your friends list, even if you only spent two hours hunting together but had a good experience with the person, chances are, he's out there looking for a group too.  If you see yourself running into the same person quite a bit in your travels, say hello once in a while, stop and chat if they are wanting to chat too. Doing this was actually how I came to be in a guild now, I kept running into this fellow everywhere I went for weeks, we would often stop and chat, I didn't realize he was an officer in his guild until he gave me an invite.  <br>
<br>
Sure, I've been on this server for a little bit now and haven't leveled very fast but I've met alot of wonderful people and enjoy the game immensely. <br>
<br>
On all other points in the original posts:<br>
/agree with Scully, well said.  <p>Narie<br>
